<div id="review_2071505820" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2071505820" />
    <a title="Maggie ☘" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40477684-maggie"><img alt="Maggie ☘" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591529603p2/40477684.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2071505820?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maggie ☘" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maggie ☘" href="/user/show/40477684-maggie">Maggie ☘</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=fairy-tale-and-other-retellings">fairy-tale-and-other-retellings</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=beautiful-writing">beautiful-writing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=intriguing-world-building">intriguing-world-building</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=hate-to-love-enemies-to-lovers">hate-to-love-enemies-to-lovers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=amazing-reads">amazing-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=great-reads-2017">great-reads-2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=great-ships">great-ships</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=high-fantasy">high-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40477684-maggie?shelf=magic">magic</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2071505820" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10627654607498387884">There&apos;s webcomic adaptation of this book (under the same name) out on Webtoons now! The art made by Silvester Vitale. I&apos;ve alread read through the episodes that are up and it&apos;s amazng! Be sure to check it out too. &lt;3<br/><br/><br/>**************************************<br/><br/>*4.5/5 stars*<br/><br/><i>
  <b>“A true plague of a girl. And yet a queen in every sense of the word.”</b>
</i><br/><br/>Such a beautifully written fairy tale. I loved the story, the romance and how the world was depicted. I had some problems here and there, but it was just such </span>
  <span id="freeText10627654607498387884" style="display:none">There's webcomic adaptation of this book (under the same name) out on Webtoons now! The art made by Silvester Vitale. I've alread read through the episodes that are up and it's amazng! Be sure to check it out too. &lt;3<br /><br /><br />**************************************<br /><br />*4.5/5 stars*<br /><br /><i>
  <b>“A true plague of a girl. And yet a queen in every sense of the word.”</b>
</i><br /><br />Such a beautifully written fairy tale. I loved the story, the romance and how the world was depicted. I had some problems here and there, but it was just such an enticing quiet tale. <br />Exquisite writing style. Compelling change of POVs. Delicious food. Descriptions of clothes and culture. A few moments which tug at some heartstrings. Great female friendship (loved Despina) and addictive romance. <br /><br /><i>
  <b>“She was a dangerous, dangerous girl. A plague. A Mountain of Adamant who tore the iron from ships, sinking them to their watery graves without a second thought. With a mere smile and a wrinkle of her nose.”</b>
</i><br /><br />I had some problems with the pace, it was mostly slower read until the last part of the book, which I couldn't stop reading. I loved the flowery writing style and think it really fits the story, but I know that it's not for everyone. It took me some time to warm to Khalid's character, but when I did I fell in love with him and Shahrzad. <br /><br /><i>
  <b>“It’s a fitting punishment for a monster. to want something so much—to hold it in your arms — and know beyond a doubt you will never deserve it.”</b>
</i><br /><br />Shahrzad is a great heroine. Sometimes her behavior was a bit spoiled, though not enough for me to dislike her. I kept hearing in reviews how intelligent and cunning Shazi is and while I do think she is clever, I expect more from her in the sequel. <br />Despina and Jalal were a great duo. I wasn't the biggest fan of Tariq and the promise of a love triangle. I have my ship and don't want anyone to to get in the way of it.<br /><br /><i>
  <b>“My soul sees its equal in you.”</b>
</i><br /><br />All in all, a beautiful story with rich descriptions of food, clothing and culture, obviously very much romance centered, with mostly slow pace and intrigue. Hopefully, I will enjoy the sequel just as much.<br /><br /><i>
  <b>“We women are a sad lot, aren't we?"<br />"What do you mean?"<br />"Strong enough to take on the world with our bare hands, yet we permit ridiculous boys to make fools of us."<br />"I am not a fool."<br />"No, you're not. Not yet.”</b>
</i><br /><br /><br /><i>
  <b>“So you would have me throw Shazi to the wolves?”<br />“Shazi?” Jalal’s grin widened. “Honestly, I pity the wolves.”</b>
</i><br /><br /><br />************************************<br /><br />I'm very excited for this one! Hopefully the inside of this book will be just as stunning as the outside is! ♥<br /><br />My first <i>A Thousand and One Nights</i> retelling, here we go!<br /><br />Buddy read with the lovely <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/19846410-ivusha" rel="nofollow noopener">Ivusha</a>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10627654607498387884" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

